raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "dart-sass" %}
{% set version = "1.54.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  - url: https://github.com/sass/dart-sass/archive/refs/tags/{{ version }}.tar.gz                                      # [not osx or not arm64]
    sha256: fbfe1590ef63998b62d108b2dd848ea71456e910c50405b0ae7fadc43212472b                                           # [not osx or not arm64]
  - url: https://github.com/sass/dart-sass/releases/download/{{ version }}/dart-sass-{{ version }}-macos-arm64.tar.gz  # [osx and arm64]
    sha256: 686dc8efa370f050668c87a6a7762f8a6e5e8fbf85c2361d727ce860b3f509df                                           # [osx and arm64]

build:
  number: 2
  binary_relocation: False
  missing_dso_whitelist:
    # normal linux stuff that would go away if we had libgcc-ng in the run deps
    - '*/ld-linux.so.2'
    - '*/lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2'
    - '*/libpthread.so.0'
    - '*/libdl.so.2'
    - '*/libm.so.6'
    - '*/libc.so.6'

requirements:
  host:
    - dart-sdk       # [unix and not arm64]
    - nodejs >=18    # [win]
  run:
    - nodejs         # [win]

test:
  files:
    - test.sass
  commands:
    - sass test.sass output.css

about:
  home: https://sass-lang.com/dart-sass
  license: MIT
  license_file:
    - LICENSE           # [not osx or not arm64]
    - src/LICENSE       # [osx and arm64]
  summary: Dart implementation of Sass. Sass makes CSS fun again.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - msarahan
